The basic idea is to decrease the search space. Now, what does this mean, Actually if we want to place a number at the first position then it will be having (n-1)! ways to do it. So, let us take an example:

n = 4 and k=9

so, for suppose if we assume our answer will be having '1' at 1st position. Now let us write the possibilites:

1 2 3 4
1 2 4 3
1 3 2 4
1 3 4 2
1 4 2 3
1 4 3 2

and our k value is 9 but the number of possible ways with 1 are only 6. So 1 can't be at first position.

Now let us check for '2' but this time our k will be (9-6 = 3) [beacuse we will not again look into possiblilites of '1'].

if we take 2 then 3-6<0, So here we can conclude that our answer will be having 2 at it's first position. And similarly we will be checking for remaining


