# Explanation:
Everything is simple. If there is intersection, it will be on same distance from the end in both linked lists, so we just need to iterate part where potentially can have intersection. This part is last `n` elements, where `n == min(len(list1), len(list2))`.
I get length of both lists, and skip the first elements of longer one, until both lists pointers will not be on same distance to their ends. 
Here is good illustration where we should search for intersection:
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/33bedbe5-8127-488d-8a46-61b9a9ba6873_1614846291.9376721.png)
